        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Rev. DAVID LEVY&#44;<lb/>
                CHARLESTON&#44; S. C.<lb/></p>
            <p>Feby 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1883.<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd. S. Morais&#58;&#45;&#45;<lb/>
                My Dear Sir&#58;&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>Would you be kind enough<lb/> to tell me in how far Michelet is correct&#44; in say&#45;<lb/>ing that the Copernican system was known by the<lb/> Jews&#44; and is to be found in the Kabbala&#63;  Can you give me<lb/> the substance of the Rabbinic theory&#44; and where it may<lb/> be found.&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>During my visit north last summer&#44; Mendelsohn<lb/> and I spoke to Messrs Binswanger &#38; Dropsie&#44;&#45;&#45;as also<lb/> D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. Jastrow&#45;&#45;in reference to the Exfaculty of Maimonides<lb/> College&#44; granting us a diploma&#44; and a degree&#44; as<lb/> provided for in the charter given the Hebrew Educa&#45;<lb/>tion Society by the Legislature.  Do you know whether<lb/> the matter has been broached at all&#63;  We have<lb/> found it&#44; at times&#44; quite a disadvantage&#44; in being<lb/> without any evidence of <del>having received</del> such kind<lb/></p>
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>and while the Faculty is still in the land of the<lb/> living it would be opportune to obtain their views on the<lb/> subject.  Mr Dropsie &#38; Binswanger were quite fa&#45;<lb/>vorable to the idea of granting us the document &#38;<lb/> degree&#44; while D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Jastrow hesitated in giving an opinion<lb/> Pray&#44; what is your idea&#63;  Mendelsohn &#38; myself<lb/> thought of making &#38; joint application.  I find that the<lb/> authority for granting such such diploma &#38;c is vested with<lb/> <hi rend="underline">the faculty</hi> &#38; not the Trustees.  If we should decide<lb/> to address the Ex&#45;faculty on the subject&#44; and if you<lb/> are favorably disposed towards the <del>the</del> application<lb/> may I bespeak your kind influence &#38; interest&#63;<lb/>  With kindest regards<lb/> Yours Sincerely<lb/> D. Levy.<lb/></p>
        </body>
